to the editor as others abandon plains indians and bison come back front page may 27 provides solid evidence that although the land may be temporarily corraled parceled out and diked by human beings it eventually recovers and reclaims its status as that which we are dependent on i disagree however with the assertion that european agricultural settlement may have been an accident of history or perhaps only a chapter there was nothing accidental about the various federal indian and environmental policies that practically destroyed the native people of the great plains and the flora and fauna of that impressive ecological landscape david e wilkins minneapolis may 28 2001 the writer is an associate professor of american indian studies university of minnesota

